qas.question: Where did Mary first meet the angel Gabriel?

plausible_answers.text: Hebron, in the hill country of Judah

qas.question: Where did Elizabeth first meet Zechariah?
What did the angel Gabriel tell Elizabeth whom Mary was?

context: Since the angel Gabriel had told Mary (according to Luke 1:36) that Elizabeth—having previously been barren—was then miraculously pregnant, Mary hurried to see Elizabeth, who was living with her husband Zechariah in "<b1_0><b2_0>Hebron, in the hill country of Judah<b2_0/><b1_0/>". Mary arrived at the house and greeted Elizabeth who called Mary "<b4_0>the mother of my Lord<b4_0/>", and Mary spoke the words of praise that later became known as the Magnificat from her first word in the <b0_0><b3_0>Latin<b3_0/><b0_0/> version.[Luke 1:46-55] After about three months, Mary returned to her own house.[Lk 1:56-57]
